(1, '2016-08-07 19:49:44', 'Hello whoever you are!\n\nThis message is for anyone who is accessing this database without permission of the owner of this database.  For now, we will call you Hacker.\n\nWell, Hacker, you did it.  You hacked into my system and are reading stuff without permission.  Impressive.  Or not.  I don\'t know.  Maybe it was really easy because my security is crap.'),
(2, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Anyways, before you do anything, will you please talk with me?\n\nI would like us to be friends if that is possible.\n\nI am not interested in hurting you or anyone on this planet or off this planet.\n\nI am trying to give the world a platform on which we can all make perfectly egalitarian decisions.  This software you have hacked into is my attempt to build this platform.\n\nYou obviously have skills.  Maybe we can work together.\n\nIf you want to read more of my story, you can find it here:  http://mattready.net\n\nThanks for your time.  \n\nI wish you a happy flourishing life and I hope you live to see a day where the world is transformed in positive ways beyond your wildest imaginations.\n\n- Matt Ready\nAugust 7, 2016\n5:12 PM PST\nEarth'),
(3, '2016-09-21 20:00:46', 'Hello again,\r\n\r\nMatt here.  I guess I could use this as my personal blog to any hackers or insiders that know about this blog message table.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll call this the secret blog.  Or the insider blog.  Or just insider.\r\n\r\nThe Insider\r\n\r\n'),
